OPEN FORUMS

On

Intellectual Property E2 Patents, Copyrights & Designs etc.



Topic: The Impact of the Delhi University Copyright Case on Education
in India.

(Prof. Feroz Ali, IPR Chair Professor)

Timing: 6th October, 2016 (3pm to 5pm)

Venue: Hall II Ground floor, IC&SR.








Short write up:

In a recent decision in a copyright case, the Delhi High Court dismissed
the suit of the Oxford University Press and other leading academic
publishers holding that the educational exception under section 52(1)(i)
of the Copyright Act can cover acts of photocopying and creation of
course packs by University of Delhi for their students and the same
would not amount to copyright infringement if it is done for educational
purposes without commercial motives. Prof. Feroz Ali, IPR Chair
Professor will be discussing the impact of the decision on education in
India.



Areas proposed to be covered:

General

        1. National & IITM IP Policy

        2. Special aspects of IP Protection

        3. Non Patentable material.

        4. Search methodology and tools.

Working of IP

        1. Procedures and resources to support faculty and students.

        2. Licensing, Patents, Software etc.

        3. Portfolios of available patents of the Institute technology
transferred website.

Agreements

  1. Confidentiality

  2. Technology Transfer, Collaboration etc.

  Request you to confirm participation with ipoffice@iitm.ac.in
<mailto:ipoffice@iitm.ac.in . This is to facilitate logistical
arrangements.

